A mass of 1 kg of saturated water vapor at $100^degree C$ completely condenses into liquid water by transferring heat to the surrounding air, which remains at a constant temperature of $25^degree C$. The system reaches absolute thermal equilibrium at the end of the process. Given the latent heat of vaporization is $h = 2260 times 10^3 " J/kg"$, what is the total entropy change of the universe ($Delta S_"tot"$)?

